Class MouseClickEvent

java.lang.Object
  org.icesoft.testclient.event.MouseClickEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
ButtonPressEvent, LoginEvent, SendTextEvent
public class MouseClickEvent
extends java.lang.Object
implements Event

MouseClickEvent is an implementation of Event that does all the encoding of parameters for a mouseClick. Construct this object and use the API to define variations on the basic theme such as alt, ctrl, right mouse, etc, and this object uses the Client to take care of encoding itself to the URLConnection.
